{"id":470,"date":"2023-12-30T11:29:22","date_gmt":"2023-12-30T11:29:22","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/clouds.digitalskeleton.com.ng\/?p=470"},"modified":"2023-12-30T11:39:51","modified_gmt":"2023-12-30T11:39:51","slug":"penetration-testing-techniques","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/clouds.digitalskeleton.com.ng\/index.php\/2023\/12\/30\/penetration-testing-techniques\/","title":{"rendered":"PENETRATION TESTING TECHNIQUES"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><br><strong>Network Penetration Testing<\/strong> is a security service that identifies security vulnerabilities in networks, systems, hosts, and devices by purposefully using malicious techniques to test the network\u2019s security responses. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>It is a crucial step in ensuring the security of your network. Penetration testing can help businesses obtain expert, unbiased third-party feedback on their security processes. It is recommended that businesses consult with experts before pen testing to ensure that testing does not damage the network and to obtain better insights into vulnerabilities. Cisco offers a range of products and services that can help with pen testing.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are several common network vulnerabilities that can be exploited by attackers to gain unauthorized access to a network. Here are some of the most common ones:<br><strong>Unpatched software<\/strong>: Outdated software can contain security vulnerabilities that can be exploited by attackers to gain access to a network.<br><strong>Weak passwords<\/strong>: Weak passwords can be easily guessed or cracked by attackers, allowing them to gain access to a network.<br><strong>Misconfigured firewalls<\/strong>: Misconfigured firewalls can allow attackers to bypass network security measures and gain access to a network.<br><strong>Unsecured wireless networks<\/strong>: Unsecured wireless networks can be easily accessed by attackers, allowing them to intercept network traffic and gain access to sensitive information.<br><strong>Phishing attacks<\/strong>: Phishing attacks can trick users into revealing sensitive information such as login credentials, which can then be used by attackers to gain access to a network..<br><strong>Malware<\/strong>: Malware can be used to gain unauthorized access to a network, steal sensitive information, or cause damage to a network.<br><strong>Social engineering<\/strong>: Social engineering attacks can trick users into revealing sensitive information or performing actions that can compromise network security.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><br>It is important to note that this is not an exhaustive list of network vulnerabilities. To ensure the security of your network, it is recommended that you consult with experts before pen testing to obtain better insights into vulnerabilities.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are some best practices to protect your network from common vulnerabilities:<br><strong>Keep software up to date<\/strong>: Regularly update software to ensure that security vulnerabilities are patched<br><strong>Use strong passwords<\/strong>: Use strong, unique passwords and enable two-factor authentication where possible.<br><strong>Configure firewalls correctly<\/strong>: Ensure that firewalls are configured correctly to prevent unauthorized access to your network.<br><strong>Secure wireless networks<\/strong>: Secure wireless networks with strong encryption and use a separate network for guests.<br><strong>Educate employees<\/strong>: Educate employees on how to identify and avoid phishing attacks and other social engineering tactics.<br><strong>Use anti-malware software<\/strong>: Use anti-malware software to detect and remove malware from your network.<br><strong>Implement access controls<\/strong>: Implement access controls to ensure that only authorized users have access to sensitive data.<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition to these best practices, it is recommended that you consult with experts to obtain better insights into vulnerabilities and to ensure that your network is secure. Microsoft Azure offers a range of products and services that can help with network security.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Network Penetration Testing is a security service that identifies security vulnerabilities in networks, systems, hosts, and devices by purposefully using malicious techniques to test the network\u2019s security responses. It is&#8230;.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":473,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[1],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-470","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-wireless-cloud-penetration-testing"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/clouds.digitalskeleton.com.ng\/index.php\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/470","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/clouds.digitalskeleton.com.ng\/index.php\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/clouds.digitalskeleton.com.ng\/index.php\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/clouds.digitalskeleton.com.ng\/index.php\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/clouds.digitalskeleton.com.ng\/index.php\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=470"}],"version-history":[{"count":4,"href":"https:\/\/clouds.digitalskeleton.com.ng\/index.php\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/470\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":477,"href":"https:\/\/clouds.digitalskeleton.com.ng\/index.php\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/470\/revisions\/477"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/clouds.digitalskeleton.com.ng\/index.php\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/473"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/clouds.digitalskeleton.com.ng\/index.php\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=470"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/clouds.digitalskeleton.com.ng\/index.php\/wp-js